; Minimal test case for Beancount pad auto-generation behavior
;
; This file demonstrates that loader.load_file() automatically generates
; a padding transaction when it encounters a pad directive followed by
; a balance assertion.
;
; Expected behavior:
; 1. File on disk contains only pad directive and balance assertion
; 2. loader.load_file() returns an auto-generated Transaction with flag 'P'
; 3. If all entries are written back using printer.format_entry(),
;    the auto-generated padding transaction gets written to the file
; 4. This causes bean-check to warn about "Unused Pad entry"

2020-01-01 open Assets:Test USD
2020-01-01 open Equity:Opening-Balances

; The pad directive tells Beancount to automatically balance this account
2023-12-31 pad Assets:Test Equity:Opening-Balances

; The balance assertion defines what the balance should be
2024-01-01 balance Assets:Test 1000.00 USD
